               <p>SAMUEL CHALLIS. I lodged in <placeName id="t18310217-202-crimeloc1203">Bainbridge-street, St. Giles</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-202-crimeloc1203" type="placeName" value="Bainbridge-street, St. Giles"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-202-crimeloc1203" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-202-off1201 t18310217-202-crimeloc1203"></join>, for about three months - the prisoner lodged there. On the 27th of December I had a coat given me; 1 hung it on a line - on getting up the next morning I missed it, about the dawn of that day - the prisoner had gone out at five o'clock that morning; he had lodged in the same room - I did not see him again till the 6th of January, when I met him in Buckeridge-street; I seized him - he said he was very sorry for what had occurred, and he would make it up by giving me something to eat; he was taken to the watch-house, and said he had borrowed the coat of Kitchener, who lodged in the house.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-202-person1921">
                  THOMAS 
                  KITCHENER
               <interp inst="t18310217-202-person1921" type="surname" value="KITCHENER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-202-person1921" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-202-person1921" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lodge in the same room with the prosecutor. I missed a coat and shirt on the 28th of December - I have seen them in the officer's possession; the shirt was by the fire, and the prisoner asked me to lend him the coat to throw over his bed.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. The coat and shirt were lent to me. Witness. I only lent him the coat to throw over his bed - I did not lend the shirt at all.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-202-person1922">
                  JOHN 
                  REEVE
               <interp inst="t18310217-202-person1922" type="surname" value="REEVE"></interp>
